в””в”Җв”Җ c_runs/ # C++ model checkpoints (.pt)

---

Python Training

cd /PINN
python src/run_experiments.py

Output: checkpoints in runs/, logs in py_logs/, plots in all_plots/py_experiments/

---

C++ Training (LibTorch)

Requirements: GCC 12.3.0, CMake 3.25.2, LibTorch

module load gcc/12.3.0
module load cmake/3.25.2

cd /PINN/cpp
make -f make_experiments LIBTORCH=/fs/scratch/PAS2137/libtorch

Run all 8 experiments:

(If on OSC:
sinteractive -A PAS2137 -c 32 -t 01:00:00)

build/bin/pinn_experiments

Output: checkpoints in c*runs/, logs in c_logs/, eval results in c_logs/evals.csv,
per-epoch loss in c_logs/loss*\*.csv

---

Plotting C++ Results

cd /PINN
python src/plot_cpp_experiments.py

Output: all_plots/cpp_experiments/ - 8 loss curve graphs (skipped if loss CSVs not yet generated) - 2 error bar charts (heat, burgers) - 8 per-epoch timing graphs - 1 Python vs C++ training time comparison
